cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NI, cs.CC 

This paper proposes a new score function for stack decoding of polar codes, which is a technique used in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with decoding algorithms, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses complexity reduction, which could be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
